1 (2) Continuing NOTWITHSTANDING ANY OTHER PROVISION OF LAW,
2 CONTINUING education courses shall be taught by a qualified instructor who is
3 experienced in the real estate industry AND SELECTED BY THE COURSE PROVIDER.
4 (3) The Commission shall adopt regulations that provide for the conduct of
5 continuing education instruction courses by virtual or remote means.
6 (4) To verify the identity of an individual enrolled in a continuing education
7 course, the entity that conducts the continuing education course shall require, as a
8 condition of participating in the course, that the individual provide:
9 (i) for an in–person course, a photo identification; and
10 (ii) for a virtual or other remote course, a signed affidavit attesting
11 to the identity of the individual.
12 (d) If feasible, continuing education courses shall be offered at reasonable
13 intervals in each county and in each major geographic area of the larger counties.
14 (e) Within 14 days after completion of a continuing education course, the entity
15 that conducted the course may submit the course completion information directly to the
16 Commission and the licensee by electronic means.
17 (f) The Commission may waive the requirements of this section for a licensee if
18 the licensee shows good cause for being unable to meet the requirements.
19 (g) The Commission shall require each course provider to pay a continuing
20 education course application fee [of $25] SET BY THE COMMISSION.
